&gt; I'd recommend against tuple((a...)...) unless all elements of a always have the same size - can lead to A LOT of tuple methods to be compiled...
&gt; 
No, the beauty of this is that it won't create any intermediate tuples. Of course, overspecialization will still be an issue if the total number of elements in `a` is large, but then you probably shouldn't use tuples in the first place
